                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-213-off1180 t18300415-213-crimeloc1183"></join>, about half-past nine o'clock in the morning; I missed my pocket-handkerchief from my pocket when I got to Oxford-street - it was a new one; I had not seen the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-213-person1889">
                  WILLIAM 
                  IRELAND
               <interp inst="t18300415-213-person1889" type="surname" value="IRELAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-213-person1889" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-213-person1889" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Wimpole-street on duty; a gentleman's servant called to me, and said, "These two men have taken a handkerchief from a gentleman's pocket"- I went and took the prisoner, who Killick said had received it from the other; the prisoner took the handkerchief from his pocket, and attempted to throw it down an area; I caught it, and took him - this is it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-213-person1890">
                  HENRY 
                  KILLICK
               <interp inst="t18300415-213-person1890" type="surname" value="KILLICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-213-person1890" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-213-person1890" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner and another in Wimpole-street; I saw the other take the handkerchief from the prosecutor's pocket - the prisoner received it; they were both close to him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-213-person1891">
